<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<%= require('html-loader!./partials/head.ejs') %>
<body>
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <nav class="navbar navbar-default navbar-fixed-top">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="navbar-header">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href=""><% import logo from './assets/sf_logo_white.png'; require('file-loader!./assets/sf_logo_white.png') %> </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </div>
    <!-- nav -->
    <%= require('html-loader!./partials/welcome.ejs') %>
    <div id="view-load" class="hidden" style="margin-top: 1em;">
      Loading...
    </div>
    <div id="view-content" class="row hidden">
      <%= require('html-loader!./partials/sidebar.ejs') %>
      <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-9">
        <div class="row">
          <div id="tabs">
            <ul class="nav nav-pills">
              <li class="active">
                <a id="energy-star-tab" href="#energy-score" data-toggle="tab">LOCAL RANKING</a>
              </li>
            </ul>
            <div class="tab-content clearfix">
              <div class="tab-pane active" id="energy-score">
                <div class="row border-bottom">
                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-3">
                    <div class="row center">
                      <div class="local-ranking-container">
                        <span class="local-ranking-lg">#<span class="building-ranking-text"></span></span>
                        <br>out of <span class="total-building-type">100</span> buildings
                        <span class="center"><a data-toggle="tooltip" data-placement="right" title="The local ranking figure compares peer buildings by their ENERGY STAR Score. In cases where the rank is identical, a building's site EUI is also used. The higher a ranking, the better a building's performance.">  <i class="fa fa-info-circle" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></span>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-7">
                    <div class="estar-ranking-text">
                      Based on the ENERGY STAR score and Energy Use Intensity reported in <span class="building-energy-star-score-year">2015</span>, energy use at <span class="building-name">BUILDING NAME</span> is ranked <span class="building-ranking-text">RANK</span>											out of <span class="total-building-type">RANK NUMBER</span> <span class="building-type-lower">BUILDING TYPE</span>s between <span class="building-type-sq-ft">RANGE</span> square feet in gross floor area.
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-2"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="row center">
                  <div class="col-xs-2"></div>
                  <div class="col-xs-8">
                    <div class="chart-title">
                      LATEST ENERGY STAR SCORE FOR <span class="building-type-upper">HOTEL</span> BUILDINGS IN SAN FRANCISCO <span class="building-type-sq-ft">150,000-200,000</span> SQUARE FEET
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-2"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="row center hidden-xs">
                  <div class="col-xs-2"></div>
                  <div class="col-xs-8">
                    <!-- <div class="loading">Loading&mdash;</div> -->
                    <div id="energy-star-score-histogram" class="histogram-chart"></div>
                    <div id="demo" class="hidden">
                      <input type="number" id="change-estar-input" value="100"><button id="change-estar">change bin numbers</button>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="col-xs-2"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="col-xs-12 panel-bottom">
                    <div class="panel-bottom-header">ABOUT THE ENERGY STAR SCORE</div>
                    <br>
                    <div class="panel-bottom-text">
                      - a rating between 1-100 that summarizes at a glance how a building is performing compared to similar buildings nationwide, after accounting for local climate. The higher the score, the better; buildings with a score of 75 or better may qualify for ENERGY
                      STAR certification as top performers. The score uses the information you entered about your building, including: size, location, occupancy, number of computers, etc.
                      <br><br>
                      <div class="link"><a href="https://sfenvironment.org/article/commercial/sf-energy-watch-commercial-program">San Francisco Energy Watch can help you save money, save energy, and improve your ENERGY STAR score</a></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  </div>
  <!-- /container -->

  <script>
    $(document).ready(function() {
      $('[data-toggle="tooltip"]').tooltip();
    });
  </script>
  <script src="demo.js"></script>
</body>

</html>